Located in what used to be the old ESPN Zone, next to the HardRock Café, Phillips Crab Deck is the updated version of the Baltimore Inner Harbor Original. The original space in the Pratt Street Pavilion had charm and nostalgia with great food, but the new location keeps elements of the original decor but kicked up several notches. Love the nods to it's history (founded in 1956) as a favorite treat and celebrated destination in the Harbor.  The food is just what you want from Phillips! The favorites from generations are on the menu (seafood and crab platters, fish and chips, etc.), raw bar staples (steamed shrimp and oysters on the half shell) and the signature favorite: crab cakes! There are new offerings, desserts for every taste and still every thing is affordable enough to still be a family favorite. With the loss of Phillips in DC to urban renewal, it was nice to be able to treat my visiting friends from St. Louis who have never had a "real crab cake" to this Baltimore institution. The outdoor large patio space and new ice cream shop are sure to be a hit with tourists and locals come Spring!  Glad to see Phillips is still going strong!!

My wife had the mussels which were also good but not great but I think we both would agree the best thing we had was the cream of crab soup. With all that said I'd try it again but I'd get something different but idk how many times since the menu is so limited..
Worth a try. Portions small for price. But, passable.
